attributes.name: age
attributes.description: Person's age in years, ranging from 18 to 90+, representative of the US adult population.

attributes.name: gender
attributes.description: Gender identity of the person (Male, Female, Non-binary/Other).

attributes.name: state
attributes.description: US state of residence (all 50 states + DC), sampled proportionally to population.

attributes.name: urban_rural
attributes.description: Urbanicity of residence: Urban, Suburban, or Rural, conditioned on state population density.

attributes.name: race_ethnicity
attributes.description: Racial/ethnic identity (White non-Hispanic, Black, Hispanic, Asian, Other), representative of US census distributions.

attributes.name: education_level
attributes.description: Highest educational attainment (Less than HS, HS Diploma, Some College, Associate's, Bachelor's, Graduate Degree).

attributes.name: household_income
attributes.description: Annual household income in USD, conditioned on education level and state.

attributes.name: marital_status
attributes.description: Current marital status (Single, Married, Divorced, Widowed, Domestic Partnership).

attributes.name: household_size
attributes.description: Total number of people living in the household.

attributes.name: has_children
attributes.description: Whether the person has any children (under 18) living in the household.

attributes.name: employment_status
attributes.description: Current employment status (Full-time, Part-time, Self-employed, Unemployed, Retired, Student).

attributes.name: occupation
attributes.description: Broad occupational category (Management, Professional, Service, Sales, Construction, Production, Other) per BLS classification.

attributes.name: political_affiliation
attributes.description: Political party identification (Strong Democrat, Lean Democrat, Independent, Lean Republican, Strong Republican).

attributes.name: political_ideology
attributes.description: Self-described ideological placement on a scale (Very Liberal, Liberal, Moderate, Conservative, Very Conservative).

attributes.name: religious_affiliation
attributes.description: Religious identity (Evangelical Protestant, Mainline Protestant, Catholic, Other Christian, Jewish, Muslim, Other Non-Christian, None/Unaffiliated).

attributes.name: religious_attendance
attributes.description: Frequency of attendance at religious services (Never, Seldom, A few times/year, Monthly, Weekly, More than weekly).

attributes.name: primary_news_source
attributes.description: Primary source for national news (TV, Online/Digital, Social Media, Radio, Print Newspaper, None).

attributes.name: news_outlet_lean
attributes.description: Political lean of preferred news outlets (Left-leaning, Center, Right-leaning, Mixed/No Preference).

attributes.name: social_media_platforms
attributes.description: Primary social media platform used (Facebook, Twitter/X, Instagram, TikTok, YouTube, None/Minimal).

attributes.name: social_media_hours_per_day
attributes.description: Average daily hours spent consuming social media content.

attributes.name: internet_access
attributes.description: Quality of home internet access (Broadband, Mobile Only, Dial-up/Satellite, None).

attributes.name: civic_engagement
attributes.description: Level of civic participation (Votes regularly, Votes sometimes, Rarely votes/Never votes, Also actively volunteers or campaigns).

attributes.name: homeownership
attributes.description: Whether the household owns (vs. rents) their primary residence.

attributes.name: health_insurance_type
attributes.description: Type of health insurance coverage (Employer-sponsored, Medicaid/CHIP, Medicare, Individual Market/ACA, Military/VA, Uninsured).

attributes.name: immigration_status
attributes.description: Citizenship and immigration status (US-born citizen, Naturalized citizen, Permanent resident, Other).

attributes.name: union_membership
attributes.description: Whether the person is currently a member of a labor union.

attributes.name: gun_ownership
attributes.description: Whether the household contains at least one firearm.

attributes.name: openness
attributes.description: Big Five openness to experience: curiosity, creativity, and willingness to consider new ideas (0–1 scale).

attributes.name: conscientiousness
attributes.description: Big Five conscientiousness: organization, dependability, and self-discipline (0–1 scale).

attributes.name: extraversion
attributes.description: Big Five extraversion: sociability, assertiveness, and positive emotionality (0–1 scale).

attributes.name: agreeableness
attributes.description: Big Five agreeableness: cooperation, empathy, and trust toward others (0–1 scale).

attributes.name: neuroticism
attributes.description: Big Five neuroticism: emotional instability, anxiety, and negative affect (0–1 scale).

attributes.name: trust_in_institutions
attributes.description: Generalized trust in government, media, and public institutions (0–1 scale, low = high distrust).

attributes.name: need_for_cognition
attributes.description: Tendency to engage in and enjoy effortful analytical thinking when forming opinions (0–1 scale).

attributes.name: susceptibility_to_misinformation
attributes.description: Propensity to accept and share unverified or false information, inversely related to media literacy (0–1 scale).
